{
  "texts": [
    "As AI models are increasingly applied to the creation of new compounds for use in food, fragrance, and therapeutic settings, these outputs may include chemical combinations that have not undergone thorough human testing.",
    "Existing safety evaluation frameworks may fall short when assessing such AI-generated formulations, particularly when the results differ significantly from familiar sensory profiles.",
    "To ensure safety, a multidisciplinary approach is required.",
    "This should involve expertise from food science, toxicology, pharmacology, and AI interpretability.",
    "The goal is to confirm that novel sensory outputs do not unintentionally introduce allergens, toxic substances, or other health hazards."
  ]
}